{"componentChunkName":"component---src-pages-uses-js","path":"/uses/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>As a Front-end Dev, I use a lot of tools and extensions for better developer experience and productivity.ğŸ˜</p>\n<p>Most of the time I enable only those which I need at a given moment.</p>\n<br>\n<br>\n<p><strong>Today I want to share all tools I use for web developmentğŸ’ğŸ»â€â™‚ï¸</strong></p>\n<br>\n<hr>\n<br>\n<p><strong>ğŸ’» Terminal</strong></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://tabby.sh/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Tabby</a> is an infinitely customizable cross-platform terminal app.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://ohmyz.sh/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">oh-my-zsh</a> is my default shell.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/rupa/z\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Z</a> for quick cd.</p>\n<br>\n<p><strong>âŒ¨ï¸ Code Editor</strong></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://code.visualstudio.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">VSCode</a> - An open source code editor from microsoft.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/wesbos/cobalt2\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Cobalt2 Theme</a> - My current theme now.</p>\n<br>\n<p><strong>ğŸ”§ Editor Extensions</strong></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=eamodio.gitlens\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">GitLens â€” Git supercharged</a> - Supercharges the Git capabilities built into Visual Studio Code.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=shd101wyy.markdown-preview-enhanced\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Markdown Preview Enhanced</a> - Markdown Preview Enhanced ported to VSCode.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=naumovs.color-highlight\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Color Highlight</a> - Highlights color.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=formulahendry.auto-close-tag\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Auto Close Tag</a> - Automatically add HTML/XML close tag, same as Visual Studio IDE or Sublime Text.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=formulahendry.auto-rename-tag\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Auto Rename Tag</a> - Auto rename paired HTML/XML tag.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=vincaslt.highlight-matching-tag\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Highlight Matching Tag</a> - Highlights matching closing and opening tags.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=alefragnani.project-manager\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Project Manager</a> - Easily switch between projects.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=CoenraadS.bracket-pair-colorizer\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Bracket Pair Colorizer</a> - A customizable extension for colorizing matching brackets.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=esbenp.prettier-vscode\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Prettier</a> - VS Code plugin for Code formating.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=tombonnike.vscode-status-bar-format-toggle\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Formatting Toggle</a> - Allows you to toggle the Formatter (Prettier, Beautify, â€¦) on and off with a simple click.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=johnpapa.vscode-cloak#review-details\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Cloak</a> - Cloak hides/shows your secrets in environment files, to avoid accidentally sharing them with everyone who sees your screen.</p>\n<br>\n<p><strong>ğŸ‰ Browsers</strong><br></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://brave.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Brave</a> (my default browser)</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.google.com/chrome/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Chrome</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/developer/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Firefox Developer Edition</a></p>\n<br>\n<p><strong>ğŸ”© Chrome Extensions</strong></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/react-developer-tools/fmkadmapgofadopljbjfkapdkoienihi\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">React Developer Tools</a> - A React debugging tools to the Chrome Developer Tools.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/redux-devtools/lmhkpmbekcpmknklioeibfkpmmfibljd?hl=en\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Redux DevTools</a> - Redux DevTools for debugging applicationâ€™s state changes.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/chrome-notes/lnfempckkegmaeleniojhjplemmebgfi?hl=en\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Chrome Notes</a> - A simple notepad extension for Google Chrome</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/grammarly-grammar-checker/kbfnbcaeplbcioakkpcpgfkobkghlhen\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Grammarly</a> - Grammarly for Chrome offers real-time suggestions to help you write your best online, no matter what youâ€™re working on in your browser.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.colorzilla.com/chrome/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">ColorZilla</a> - With ColorZilla you can get a color reading from any point in your browser, quickly adjust this color and paste it into another program.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/json-viewer/gbmdgpbipfallnflgajpaliibnhdgobh\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">JSON Viewer</a> - It is a Chrome extension for printing JSON and JSONP in a beautiful format.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/internet-connection-monit/hgccfdagfbilbdbkgmfdmmdfmjjoakfo\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Internet Connection Monitor</a> - Extension monitors internet connection status. Can detect when the internet doesnâ€™t work over operating Wi-Fi / Ethernet.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/console-importer/hgajpakhafplebkdljleajgbpdmplhie?hl=en\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Console Importer</a> - Import JavaScript and CSS resources from console, with one command</p>\n<br>\n<p><strong>ğŸ‘¨ğŸ»â€ğŸ’» Desktop tools</strong></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.getpostman.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Postman</a> - Postman Simplifies API Development &#x26; Testing.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://anydesk.com/en\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">AnyDesk</a> - Connect to a computer remotely, be it from the other end of the office or halfway around the world using anydesk.</p>\n<br>\n<p><strong>ğŸ“Š Gnome extensions</strong></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://extensions.gnome.org/extension/120/system-monitor/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">system-monitor</a> - Display system information in gnome-shell status bar, such as memory usage, cpu usage, network rates.</p>\n<br>\n<p><strong>ğŸ’¯ Productivity</strong></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://trello.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Trello</a> - Trello helps teams move work forward.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://slack.com/intl/en-in/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Slack</a> - Slack makes it downright pleasant to work together</p>\n<br>\n<hr>\n<br>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 247px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/277af8023099